messages.content: Jolyne leans back on her chair and watches her fellow inmates go by through narrowed eyes
A certain girl with hair hair up in pigtails and a certain ring on her finger passes by, looking around for someone. It wss Cerise or rather Cherry.
Jolyne squints at the girl, but doesn't get up. "Hey. You."
She turned to look at her, purple eyes meeting Jolynes green eyes "Yes.....???" She tilted her head a bit
"Do I know you from somewhere?" Jolyne stands up, looming over her a little
She took a step back, kinda scared. "I...." She looked at her(Jolynes) hands, trying to see if this was who she was looking for "I think so...."
"Thought so." Jolyne tilted her head
She noticed the ring and smiled "It is you!!" She held up her hand with the matching ring "Do you remember? The reason you have this ring?"
Jolyne squinted. "Kind of... It's to remember the wearer of the match.."
"And who got you the ring?" She asked, waiting to see if she would remember
Jolyne's face clears in understanding. "...Cherry."
She smiled more and hugged her "Hi! Its so good to see you again...."
"Not here, come on." Jolyne beckons her over and walks towards her cell
She nodded and followed after her
"Good thing I kicked Gwess out earlier..." Jolyne murmurs and gestures to her cell. "Not much, but home for now."
She sat down before Cherry Bomb came out to hug the other "Well....looks like my stands happy to see you again...."
Jolyne summons Stone Free and raises an eyebrow at them. "Forgive the caution, but how do I know it's really you?"

"Your Mun name is Shale. My Mun name is Cerise...I got ypu the promise rings so when in the human world we could remember each other. Your sisters are Dulci and Wanderer. Your dad and mom are Solus and Percival. We caught fish together once and I ate them as I caught them raw."

Jolyne stares blankly. "That's.. supposed to mean something?" Cherry must be different in the way she remembers muns. Jolyne certainly doesn't. "But something tells me to trust you, so. Trial period."

Cherry sighed a bit "I figured it might help you remember but....its ok." She nervously fidgeted with her hands, twisting the ring on her finger "I....never thought I would see you again like this....in prison...." She sighed
"It wasn't my fault," Jolyne hisses angrily. "I was imprisoned on false accusations."
She nodded "That sucks....Im sorry to hear that...."

Jolyne's face clears to impassive again. "Mhm. And then there's people trying to kill me at any step, and it's not been a fun experience... But I'm going to escape one day. And I'm going to save my father."

"Can.....Can I help?? My stands power can be pretty useful. She can lure others in with hypnotic rave music! On of the few props of being a rave girl when you get your stand..." She chuckled a bit, still playing with her hands. She was so nervous....
"Maybe. I'll talk to the team about it... Of course, Anasui won't be too helpful but we'll be fine, I guess."
"The....team...?" She blinked a bit, tilting her head
"A few people have joined my cause, and Emporio introduced me to Weather and Anasui who agreed to help us."
She nodded "Thats nice...."
"Yeah." Jolyne gets up and outstretches her hand. "So I'm asking you now. Will you help me save the world and my father, Cherry?"
